Surinder,

Since the reactor object stores its state internally, changing the 
state of the gas won&#39;t change the state of the reactor.  The gas object 
is used by the reactor object to compute properties, but it sets it to 
its internally-stored state first.

The best thing to do is to start a new simulation (i.e. create a new 
reactor) in the state you want with the added water.


